The paper involves the use of deep neural networks for classification tasks, which is a common topic in the machine learning subfield of computer science (cs.LG). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs) suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.NE) applications, respectively. The use of attribution methods to interpret the network's decision criteria suggests a focus on explainable AI (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
